<figureCitation box="[919,946,740,762]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–39" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[291,1287,385,1614]" captionTargetId="figure-122@16.[281,1307,381,1621]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37–39. Xanthopygus oliveirae Lynch. 37. Habitus photograph. 38. Pronotum. 39. Antenna. The pronotum of this specimen is depressed dorsally (probably due to preservation). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6048509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6048509/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">37</figureCitation>
