</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,710,1495]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
- Antennomere 3 subequal to 2 (
<figureCitation box="[531,604,945,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–39" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[291,1287,385,1614]" captionTargetId="figure-122@16.[281,1307,381,1621]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37–39. Xanthopygus oliveirae Lynch. 37. Habitus photograph. 38. Pronotum. 39. Antenna. The pronotum of this specimen is depressed dorsally (probably due to preservation). Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6048509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6048509/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
); pronotum microsculpture with transverse lines; tergite 6 densely punctate; no male specimens known............................................................................ 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1436,974,996]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xanthopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oliveirae">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,974,996]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">X. oliveirae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,710,1495]" pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
<keyLead pageId="25" pageNumber="176">
